The metre of the ode has given much trouble to Commentators, especially to those who insist upon the theory that all Horace's odes are reducible to quatrain stanzas, while this ode is in a stanza of three lines, accord- ing to the authority of MSS. (with the exception of the Turinese one). An attempt to remodel it into quatrain will be found in Orelli’s excursus to the ode, and is adopted by Yonge in his edition.
